## Voting and onboarding

- **Quota:** `CommunityDefaultsService` sets **`quotaEnabled: false`** for `typeTag === 'future-vision'` merit defaults; `quota-reset.service` forces **effective daily quota 0** for `future-vision` (see @business-merits.mdc).
- **Vote on OB post:** standard vote in the hub (merit weight per vote amounts; neutral text-only allowed when `commentMode` permits zero amount). The **first** vote row for `(userId, publication)` triggers **`ob_vote_join_offer`** (see [Notifications](#notifications)).
- **Legacy users without hub role:** `users.ensureBaseCommunities` adds roles in base/priority communities (used from Future Visions UI so voting permission works).

---

## Constraints vs regular community

| Area | `future-vision` hub (and product rules) |
|------|----------------------------------------|
| **Polls** | Creation and casting **blocked** in `polls` router when `community.typeTag === 'future-vision'`; `getByCommunity` returns **empty** for that community |
| **Withdraw** on posts | Hub bootstrap **`allowWithdraw: false`** — merits stay on posts unless DB overrides |
| **Tappalka** | No `typeTag` special-case in `TappalkaService`; MVP keeps hub **non-tappalka** via settings. ОБ “mining” in product language = **voting / rating**, not tappalka comparisons in the hub |
| **Posting** | OB posts are system-created from `futureVisionText`; users publish **in their own** communities; hub hosts the OB mirror |

---

## Relation to context switch

Publishing **as** a community (`actingAsCommunityId`) sets `sourceEntity*` on new publications elsewhere; **withdraw** to `CommunityWallet` applies for `sourceEntityType === 'community'`. That path is **orthogonal** to the OB hub feed but shares `sourceEntityType` vocabulary — see @business-projects.mdc.

---

## Notifications

| Type | When |
|------|------|
| `ob_vote_join_offer` | After **`VoteService`** creates a vote on an OB post (`publication` in hub, `sourceEntityType === 'community'`, `sourceEntityId` set), **`Vote`** count for `(userId, publicationId)` is **1** (first vote on that post). **No** `totalAmount > 0` check — a text-only neutral vote counts if the router allows it. |

Metadata keys used for redirects: `communityId` (source), `publicationId`, `publicationCommunityId`, `sourceCommunityName` (see `notification.schema.ts` / `NotificationService`).

